sources\n- AddResourceInfo() registers resources for storage version tracking\n- UpdateStorageVersions() updates StorageVersion objects in the cluster\n\n## Configuration Assembly Chain\n\n**Resource Configuration Helper** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/resourceconfig/helpers.go):\n- MergeResourceEncodingConfigs() merges default and override configurations\n- Uses SetResourceEncoding() to register specific GroupVersionResource overrides\n\n**Storage Factory Builder** (pkg/kubeapiserver/default_storage_factory_builder.go):\n- completedStorageFactoryConfig.New() assembles the storage factory\n- Integrates DefaultResourceEncoding and ResourceEncodingOverrides\n- Creates NewDefaultStorageFactory with the final resource encoding configuration\n\nThis architecture allows Kubernetes to maintain backward compatibility with v1beta1 APIs while storing objects in v1 etcd format through explicit encoding configuration, enabling gradual API migration without data corruption."
